One of the main drawbacks for full Ô¨Åne-tuning is that for each downstream task, we learn a different set of parameters ‚àÜŒ¶ whose dimension |‚àÜŒ¶| equals |Œ¶0|. Thus, if the pre-trained model is large (such as GPT-3 with |Œ¶0| ‚âà 175 Billion), storing and deploying many independent instances of Ô¨Åne-tuned models can be challenging, if at all feasible.

In this paper, we adopt a more parameter-efÔ¨Åcient approach, where the task-speciÔ¨Åc parameter increment ‚àÜŒ¶ = ‚àÜŒ¶(Œò) is further encoded by a much smaller-sized set of parameters Œò with |Œò| |Œ¶0|. The task of Ô¨Ånding ‚àÜŒ¶ thus becomes optimizing over Œò:

|y|

