Table 5: Validation accuracy on WikiSQL and MultiNLI after applying LoRA to different types of attention weights in GPT-3, given the same number of trainable parameters. Adapting both Wq and Wv gives the best performance overall. We Ô¨Ånd the standard deviation across random seeds to be consistent for a given dataset, which we report in the Ô¨Årst column.
Note that putting all the parameters in ‚àÜWq or ‚àÜWk results in signiÔ¨Åcantly lower performance, while adapting both Wq and Wv yields the best result. This suggests that even a rank of four captures enough information in ‚àÜW such that it is preferable to adapt more weight matrices than adapting a single type of weights with a larger rank.

7.2 WHAT IS THE OPTIMAL RANK r FOR LORA?
We turn our attention to the effect of rank r on model performance. We adapt {Wq, Wv}, {Wq, Wk, Wv, Wc}, and just Wq for a comparison.

